canvas.name: canvas
canvas.comment: Reference to the canvas element to which this context belongs.

drawImage.name: drawImage
drawImage.comment:
Draws an image from a CanvasImageSource to this canvas.

The entire image from dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImage.source will be drawn to this context with its top left corner at the point (dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImage.destX, dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImage.destY). If the image is larger than canvas will allow, the image will be clipped to fit the available space.

CanvasElement canvas = new CanvasElement(width: 600, height: 600);
CanvasRenderingContext2D ctx = canvas.context2D;
ImageElement img = document.query('img');

ctx.drawImage(img, 100, 100);

VideoElement video = document.query('video');
ctx.drawImage(video, 0, 0);

CanvasElement otherCanvas = document.query('canvas');
otherCanvas.width = 100;
otherCanvas.height = 100;
ctx.drawImage(otherCanvas, 590, 590); // will get clipped

See also:

  • dart-dom-html.CanvasImageSource for more information on what data is retrieved from dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImage.source.

  • drawImage from the WHATWG.

drawImageScaled.name: drawImageScaled
drawImageScaled.comment:
Draws an image from a CanvasImageSource to an area of this canvas.

The image will be drawn to this context with its top left corner at the point (dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImageScaled.destX, dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImageScaled.destY) and will be scaled to be dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImageScaled.destWidth wide and dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImageScaled.destHeight tall.

If the image is larger than canvas will allow, the image will be clipped to fit the available space.

CanvasElement canvas = new CanvasElement(width: 600, height: 600);
CanvasRenderingContext2D ctx = canvas.context2D;
ImageElement img = document.query('img');
img.width = 100;
img.height = 100;

// Scale the image to 300x50 at the point (20, 20)
ctx.drawImageScaled(img, 20, 20, 300, 50);

See also:

  • dart-dom-html.CanvasImageSource for more information on what data is retrieved from dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImageScaled.source.

  • drawImage from the WHATWG.

drawImageScaledFromSource.name: drawImageScaledFromSource
drawImageScaledFromSource.comment:
Draws an image from a CanvasImageSource to an area of this canvas.

The image is a region of dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImageScaledFromSource.source that is dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImageScaledFromSource.sourceWidth wide and dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImageScaledFromSource.destHeight tall with top left corner at (dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImageScaledFromSource.sourceX, dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImageScaledFromSource.sourceY). The image will be drawn to this context with its top left corner at the point (dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImageScaledFromSource.destX, dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImageScaledFromSource.destY) and will be scaled to be dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImageScaledFromSource.destWidth wide and dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImageScaledFromSource.destHeight tall.

If the image is larger than canvas will allow, the image will be clipped to fit the available space.

VideoElement video = document.query('video');
video.width = 100;
video.height = 100;
// Take the middle 20x20 pixels from the video and stretch them.
ctx.drawImageScaledFromSource(video, 40, 40, 20, 20, 50, 50, 100, 100);

// Draw the top 100x20 pixels from the otherCanvas to this one.
CanvasElement otherCanvas = document.query('canvas');
ctx.drawImageScaledFromSource(otherCanvas, 0, 0, 100, 20, 0, 0, 100, 20);

See also:

  • dart-dom-html.CanvasImageSource for more information on what data is retrieved from dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImageScaledFromSource.source.

  • drawImage from the WHATWG.

drawImageToRect.name: drawImageToRect
drawImageToRect.comment:
Draws an image from a CanvasImageSource to an area of this canvas.

The image will be drawn to an area of this canvas defined by dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImageToRect.destRect. dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImageToRect.sourceRect defines the region of the source image that is drawn. If dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImageToRect.sourceRect is not provided, then the entire rectangular image from dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImageToRect.source will be drawn to this context.

If the image is larger than canvas will allow, the image will be clipped to fit the available space.

CanvasElement canvas = new CanvasElement(width: 600, height: 600);
CanvasRenderingContext2D ctx = canvas.context2D;
ImageElement img = document.query('img');
img.width = 100;
img.height = 100;

// Scale the image to 20x20.
ctx.drawImageToRect(img, new Rectangle(50, 50, 20, 20));

VideoElement video = document.query('video');
video.width = 100;
video.height = 100;
// Take the middle 20x20 pixels from the video and stretch them.
ctx.drawImageToRect(video, new Rectangle(50, 50, 100, 100),
    sourceRect: new Rectangle(40, 40, 20, 20));

// Draw the top 100x20 pixels from the otherCanvas.
CanvasElement otherCanvas = document.query('canvas');
ctx.drawImageToRect(otherCanvas, new Rectangle(0, 0, 100, 20),
    sourceRect: new Rectangle(0, 0, 100, 20));

See also:

  • dart-dom-html.CanvasImageSource for more information on what data is retrieved from dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.drawImageToRect.source.

  • drawImage from the WHATWG.

fillText.name: fillText
fillText.comment:
Draws text to the canvas.

The text is drawn starting at coordinates (dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.fillText.x, dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.fillText.y). If dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.fillText.maxWidth is provided and the dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.fillText.text is computed to be wider than dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.fillText.maxWidth, then the drawn text is scaled down horizontally to fit.

The text uses the current dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.font property for font options, such as typeface and size, and the current dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.fillStyle for style options such as color. The current dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.textAlign and CanvasRenderingContext2D.textBaseLine properties are also applied to the drawn text.

setFillColorHsl.name: setFillColorHsl
setFillColorHsl.comment: Sets the color used inside shapes. dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.setFillColorHsl.h is in degrees, 0-360. dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.setFillColorHsl.s, dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.setFillColorHsl.l are in percent, 0-100. dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.setFillColorHsl.a is 0-1.

setFillColorRgb.name: setFillColorRgb
setFillColorRgb.comment: Sets the color used inside shapes. dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.setFillColorRgb.r, dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.setFillColorRgb.g, dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.setFillColorRgb.b are 0-255, dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.setFillColorRgb.a is 0-1.

setStrokeColorHsl.name: setStrokeColorHsl
setStrokeColorHsl.comment: Sets the color used for stroking shapes. dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.setStrokeColorHsl.h is in degrees, 0-360. dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.setStrokeColorHsl.s, dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.setStrokeColorHsl.l are in percent, 0-100. dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.setStrokeColorHsl.a is 0-1.

setStrokeColorRgb.name: setStrokeColorRgb
setStrokeColorRgb.comment: Sets the color used for stroking shapes. dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.setStrokeColorRgb.r, dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.setStrokeColorRgb.g, dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.setStrokeColorRgb.b are 0-255, dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.setStrokeColorRgb.a is 0-1.

hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of dart-dom-html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.
